## 2. Phase 0 — Mental Model & Interview Framework <a name="phase-0"></a>

Before you learn any technology, internalize **how system design interviews are evaluated**.

### What Interviewers Are Looking For

| Dimension | Description |
|---|---|
| **Problem Clarification** | Do you ask the right questions before jumping in? |
| **Scoping** | Can you define boundaries and not over-engineer? |
| **Component Knowledge** | Do you know the tools and why to use them? |
| **Trade-off Analysis** | Can you explain pros/cons of every decision? |
| **Scalability Thinking** | Can you scale from 1K to 1B users? |
| **Communication** | Is your thought process structured and clear? |

### The RESHADED Framework (Use This in Every Interview)

```
R — Requirements (functional + non-functional)
E — Estimation (scale, storage, bandwidth)
S — Service Interface (APIs, contracts)
H — High-Level Design (components, data flow)
A — Advanced Deep Dives (bottlenecks, scaling)
D — Data Model (schema, storage choices)
E — Edge Cases (failure modes, race conditions)
D — Done? (summarize trade-offs, ask for feedback)
```

> **Tip:** Spend ~5 min on R, ~5 on E, ~5 on S, ~15–20 on H+A+D, ~5 on E+D. Total: ~45 min.

