### Week 11 — Design Storage & Infrastructure Systems

#### ✅ 11.1 Design a URL Shortener (bit.ly)

**Core Flow:**
```
POST /shorten {url: "long-url"} → short_code (7 chars)
GET /{short_code} → 301/302 Redirect to long URL
```

**ID Generation Options:**
- **Random base62:** Generate 7 random chars; check DB for collision; simple but O(1) average
- **Counter-based:** Auto-increment ID → encode as base62; no collision; distributed counter needs coordination
- **MD5/SHA hash:** Take first 7 chars; collision possible; deterministic (same URL → same code)

**Database:**
- Simple KV store: `short_code → {long_url, created_at, user_id, expiry}`
- PostgreSQL or DynamoDB
- Cache hot URLs in Redis (small dataset, power-law distribution)

**Redirect Type:**
- **301 Permanent:** Browser caches; reduces server load; analytics inaccurate (browser doesn't call short URL again)
- **302 Temporary:** Every click hits server; accurate analytics (usually preferred)

**Scale Estimates:**
- 100M URLs shortened/day = 1,150/sec writes
- 10:1 read:write → 11,500 reads/sec
- 7-char base62 = 62⁷ ≈ 3.5 trillion unique codes (plenty)

#### ✅ 11.2 Design a Distributed File Storage (S3/Dropbox)

**Key Components:**
```
Client → API Gateway → Metadata Service (SQL DB)
                   ↓
              Object Storage (chunks stored in distributed FS)
                   ↓
              Replication (3x across availability zones)
```

**Chunking:**
- Large files split into chunks (4MB each)
- Only changed chunks uploaded on sync (delta sync)
- Each chunk: content-addressed (SHA-256 of content = chunk ID)
- Deduplication: same chunk across users → stored once

**Metadata:**
- File tree structure (path, name, size, version)
- Chunk list per file version
- Stored in relational DB (ACID needed for versioning)

**Conflict Resolution:**
- Last-write-wins (simple)
- Operational Transformation (Google Docs)
- CRDTs (Conflict-free Replicated Data Types)

#### ✅ 11.3 Design a Rate Limiter Service

**Architecture:**
```
Client → API Gateway → Rate Limiter Middleware
                              ↓
                         Redis Cluster
                         (token buckets)
```

- Sliding window counter in Redis using sorted sets
- Each request: `ZADD + ZCOUNT + ZREMRANGEBYSCORE` in a Lua script (atomic)
- Return `X-RateLimit-Remaining` and `Retry-After` headers

