## 10. Estimation Cheat Sheet <a name="estimation-cheat-sheet"></a>

### Units

```
Time:        1 day = 86,400 sec ≈ 100K sec
             1 year ≈ 3.15 × 10⁷ sec ≈ 30M sec

Data:        1 char = 1 byte
             1 KB = 10³ B | 1 MB = 10⁶ B | 1 GB = 10⁹ B | 1 TB = 10¹²

Network:     1 Gbps = 10⁹ bits/sec = 125 MB/sec
             Typical server: 10 Gbps NIC
```

### Common Scale Benchmarks

```
Single DB server (PostgreSQL):  ~10K-50K reads/sec, ~5K-10K writes/sec
Redis:                          ~100K-500K ops/sec
Cassandra node:                 ~50K-100K writes/sec
Kafka partition:                ~100MB/sec throughput
CDN (Cloudflare):               50+ Tbps global capacity
```

### Sample Estimation Template

```
Traffic:
  DAU = 100M
  Posts/user/day = 2 → Write QPS = (100M × 2) / 86,400 ≈ 2,300/sec
  Peak write QPS = 2,300 × 3 (peak factor) ≈ 7,000/sec
  Read:Write ratio = 100:1 → Read QPS = 230,000/sec → Peak 700,000/sec

Storage:
  Each post: 140 bytes text + 200 bytes metadata = 340 bytes
  Daily storage: 2,300/sec × 86,400 × 340 bytes = ~67 GB/day
  5-year storage: 67 GB × 365 × 5 ≈ 120 TB

Bandwidth:
  Write: 2,300 × 340 bytes = ~780 KB/sec ≈ 1 MB/sec (negligible)
  Read: 230,000 × 340 bytes = ~78 MB/sec

Cache:
  Hot data = 20% of content serves 80% of reads
  Cache 20% of daily data: 67 GB × 0.2 ≈ 14 GB RAM needed
```

