## 11. Common Mistakes to Avoid <a name="common-mistakes"></a>

### In the Interview

- ❌ **Jumping into design without clarifying requirements** — Always ask 3–5 clarifying questions first
- ❌ **Designing for 1B users immediately** — Start simple, then scale
- ❌ **Not quantifying decisions** — "We need caching" → "We need 50GB Redis cache to serve 200K read QPS"
- ❌ **Ignoring failures** — Always address: what happens if X fails?
- ❌ **Gold-plating** — Don't design every last detail; focus on hardest problems
- ❌ **Not listening to hints** — Interviewer guidance is gold; redirect accordingly
- ❌ **Being silent** — Narrate your thought process even when thinking

### In the Design

- ❌ **Single points of failure** — Every critical component should have redundancy
- ❌ **Synchronous everything** — Async + queues for non-critical paths
- ❌ **Not using caching** — Identify read-heavy workloads; cache at multiple layers
- ❌ **Global writes to single DB** — Shard or use distributed DB early in design
- ❌ **Ignoring the network** — Minimize cross-datacenter calls; use local replicas
- ❌ **Not versioning APIs** — Always include `/v1/` in API paths

